		<td><b>Were any commercial SNES games written in C?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Although many (most?) commercial Sega Genesis games were written in 68000 assembly language, some (including Ecco, The Lion King and Sonic Spinball) were written in C.<br /><br />Are any commercial SNES games known to have been written in C (or another compiled language), or are they all believed to have used 65816 assembly?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


