	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Were any commercial SNES games written in C?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Possibilities: <ul><li>If you see C format strings, then C was likely used. NovaSquirrel found (at least a subset of) C format strings in Koei games. </li><li>Or if you see the calling conventions of a particular C compiler popular at the time, then C was likely used. </li><li>Or if you see the characteristic unoptimized instruction sequences of a particular C compiler popular at the time, then C was likely used. </li></ul>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

